headline: Earnings, Fed talk, mortgage rates, jobless claims: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton explains the biggest market stories on Thursday, July 10. Delta (DAL) and ConAgra (CAG) will report their earnings in the morning, and Levi's (LEVI) is reporting earnings after the closing bell. Fresh Fed commentary will be out, as St. Louis Fed President Alberto Musalem and San Francisco Fed President Mary Daly are both set to be delivering remarks. Freddie Mac (FMCC) is publishing weekly mortgage rate data for the week of July 3. Initial jobless claims data for the week ending July 5 will be posted. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: KBRA Assigns AA Rating to City of Salt Lake, UT Airport Revenue Bonds Series 2025A (AMT) and 2025B (Non-AMT); Affirms Rating for Parity Bonds
summary: NEW YORK, July 09, 2025--KBRA assigns a long-term rating of AA with a Stable Outlook to the Salt Lake City, Utah Airport Revenue Bonds, Series 2025A (AMT) and Airport Revenue Bonds, Series 2025B (Non-AMT). KBRA additionally affirms the long-term rating of AA for the City's outstanding Airport Revenue Bonds. The rating Outlook is Stable.
